        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): warn when --system-event on main session contains shell commands",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- `cron add --system-event \"python3 script.py\" --session main` and similar commands used to create the job silently without warning that the script text will not be executed.\n- Adds a shared `looksLikeShellCommand()` helper with a shell-command heuristic for common runtimes and relative script paths such as `./run.sh`.\n- Emits a non-blocking `stderr` warning in both `cron add` and `cron edit` when the effective session target is `main`, the payload is a `systemEvent`, and the text looks like a shell command.\n\nFixes #63107\n\n## Root Cause\n\nSystem events on the main session are dispatched as context notifications to the agent. They are not executed as shell commands. Users who pass shell command syntax via `--system-event` on `--session main` get a silently non-functional job with no indication of the limitation.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/cli/cron-cli/shared.ts`: Adds the shared shell-command heuristic.\n- `src/cli/cron-cli/register.cron-add.ts`: Warns before the `cron.add` RPC for main-session shell-looking system events.\n- `src/cli/cron-cli/register.cron-edit.ts`: Warns before the `cron.update` RPC for explicit main-session edits and existing-main jobs edited without `--session`.\n- `src/cli/cron-cli.test.ts` and `src/cli/cron-cli/shared.test.ts`: Cover add/edit warning paths, non-matches, `--session MAIN`, existing-main edit fallback, and relative script paths.\n- `CHANGELOG.md`: Adds the Unreleased Fixes entry.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Main-session cron `--system-event` payloads that look like shell commands now warn the user before the gateway RPC, so `./run.sh` is no longer accepted silently as if it would execute.\n\nReal environment tested: Local checkout of current PR head `a0e8878dfce40906653676ed616c71e2504bc33f` on 2026-05-26, running the OpenClaw source CLI through `node --import tsx src/entry.ts` with an isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME`, isolated `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, and a redacted gateway token.\n\nFocused regression tests on current head:\n\n```console\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/cron-cli.test.ts src/cli/cron-cli/shared.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.5 /Users/antonio/projects/openclaw_worktrees/pr63112_clean\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  99 passed (99)\n   Start at  15:23:16\n   Duration  1.18s (transform 838ms, setup 236ms, import 709ms, tests 118ms, environment 0ms)\n```\n\nWhitespace check on current head:\n\n```console\n$ git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\n# no output\n```\n\nExact CLI command run after this patch:\n\n```console\n$ node scripts/run-with-env.mjs \\\n  OPENCLAW_HOME=/private/tmp/openclaw_pr63112_home_current \\\n  OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/private/tmp/openclaw_pr63112_home_current/.openclaw \\\n  OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/private/tmp/openclaw_pr63112_home_current/.openclaw/openclaw.json \\\n  -- node --import tsx src/entry.ts cron add \\\n    --name proof-main-shell \\\n    --every 10m \\\n    --session main \\\n    --system-event ./run.sh \\\n    --url ws://127.0.0.1:1 \\\n    --token proof-redacted \\\n    --timeout 1000\n```\n\nCopied terminal output from the current-head CLI command above:\n\n```console\nWarning: --system-event on --session main does not execute shell commands.\n  The text is dispatched as a notification to the main agent session only.\n  To run a script, use: --message \"...\" --session isolated --wake now\nGatewayTransportError: gateway closed (1006 abnormal closure (no close frame)): no close reason\nGateway target: ws://127.0.0.1:1\nSource: cli --url\nConfig: /private/tmp/openclaw_pr63112_home_current/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\nPossible causes:\n- Gateway not yet ready to accept connections (retry after a moment)\n- TLS mismatch (connecting with ws:// to a wss:// gateway, or vice versa)\n- Gateway crashed or was terminated unexpectedly\nRun `openclaw doctor` for diagnostics.\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The warning is emitted before the gateway RPC fails, confirming the real CLI path warns users before attempting to create the job. The gateway was intentionally pointed at a local closed endpoint for this proof; the behavior under test is the pre-RPC user warning.\n\nWhat was not tested: A successful `cron.add` against a live authenticated gateway was not required for this fix because the changed behavior is the pre-RPC warning path. The focused regression suite covers the `cron edit` warning path, including edits to an existing main-session job without an explicit `--session`.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/cron-cli.test.ts src/cli/cron-cli/shared.test.ts`\n- [x] `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- [x] Current-head real CLI proof above shows `cron add --session main --system-event ./run.sh` prints the warning before the gateway RPC.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
